The paper discusses techniques for learning Bayesian networks using data, which falls under the category of artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The use of decision-graph representations for the conditional probability distributions (CPDs) suggests a focus on machine learning (cs.LG) and data mining (cs.DM). The search spaces and search procedures mentioned in the paper also suggest a focus on optimization and search algorithms, which could fall under the categories of social and information networks (cs.SI) and information theory (cs.IT).
